post_text:
School pictures for grades Pre-K to 11th grades are scheduled for Tuesday, Sept 1.
For distance learning or Spiro Virtual academy students, the high school safe room will be open from 1:00 pm to 3:00 pm. Parents can bring their students to the outside safe room door. The students' temperatures will be checked and then allowed in (if no fever) to take their school photos. Parents will not be allowed in the safe room. If students cannot take a picture this day, they will have the opportunity to take it at a later date. Senior Pictures will be taken on Thursday, Sept 3. Distance Learning/Spiro Virtual Academy Seniors need to email Mrs. Maynard for an appointment. Any other questions can also be emailed rmaynard@spiro.k12.ok.us

ELEMENTARY SUMMER INFORMATION

Attention Parents and Guardians:

Upon reviewing guidance from the Oklahoma State Department of Education and the CDC we regret to inform you that we will be unable to have any summer learning opportunities for face to face instruction for students in grades Kindergarten thru 6th at Spiro Public Schools. Our hope is that all of our students have a safe and restful summer. Until then, we will be anxiously waiting to welcome students in August!
text:
ELEMENTARY SUMMER INFORMATION

Attention Parents and Guardians:

Upon reviewing guidance from the Oklahoma State Department of Education and the CDC we regret to inform you that we will be unable to have any summer learning opportunities for face to face instruction for students in grades Kindergarten thru 6th at Spiro Public Schools. Our hope is that all of our students have a safe and restful summer. Until then, we will be anxiously waiting to welcome students in August!

Eighth and Ninth grade GEAR UP students, summer camp may have been cancelled, but you have an opportunity to attend camp virtually with GEAR UP staff and some of your favorite FOCUS trainers! Just like our usual camp, you will get to participate in activities to help strengthen goal-setting skills, team building, communication, personal branding, and even attend your virtual graduation ceremony! Contact Mrs. Hicks for more information at 918-413.3245 or bhicks2@eosc.edu.

Thank you for your patience and understanding.

post_text:
April Students of the Month
Spiro Upper Elementary Schools students of the month for April are, from left: 5th grader- Tatianah Bell, 3rd grader- Ember Mitchell, and 4th grader- Allie Ford.

Students were selected by their teachers based on the character trait of the month, Open-Minded: Students will know that people are different and may do different things. They will listen to other points of view and consider many possibilities before making a decision. They will celebrate the differences in the world.
